= The Maze
Our maze for Ratatoskr will be made up of cells measuring 18 cm per side. Previous designs used modular walls made from 16cm planks attached to posts, but the posts were held in place with Velcro instead of screws. This caused misalignment and uneven walls, which negatively affected the performance of the micromouse.

Our new design (see @MazeFloorTileDrawing) reuses the wall pieces from last year, but using their intended screw-in attachment. Each floor tile covers a 36$times$36 cm#super([2]) area, not including the connecting attachments. One such tile fits four maze cells. The posts will be screwed directly into the tiles, keeping the structure rigid and aligned. The thickness of the tiles will be between 3-5 $"mm"$ and with countersunk screw holes, these tiles will sit flush on the ground.

The tiles have been designed so that seams in the floor only run perpendicular to any path taken through the maze, so that the wheels of the micromouse cannot be caught in between two tiles.

